## 🔧 Qwen-Optimized Structured Prompts for Restyle

As of KeyShot 2026.1, the Qwen model responds best to structured, attribute-based prompts. For Restyle, the key fields are **MATERIALS**, **LIGHTING**, **COLOR**, and **STYLE** — while SUBJECT, COMPOSITION, and ENVIRONMENT remain inherited from the base render.

### Structured Restyle Template

```
MATERIALS: [target surface types, finishes, roughness, reflectivity]
LIGHTING: [light source, direction, softness, temperature, contrast]
COLOR: [dominant palette, accent hues, saturation]
STYLE: [aesthetic treatment, visual medium]
QUALITY: [detail level, realism target]
EXCLUSIONS: [unwanted artifacts or styles]
```

### Example: Luxury Tech Restyle

**Structured:**
```
MATERIALS: brushed anodized aluminum, matte black polymer, frosted glass accents
LIGHTING: soft key light from upper left, subtle rim light, controlled shadow falloff
COLOR: gunmetal gray, deep navy accents, cool silver highlights
STYLE: premium product photography, clean industrial aesthetic
QUALITY: ultra-detailed, high realism, crisp material definition
EXCLUSIONS: no color bleed, no plastic-looking surfaces, no oversaturation
```

**Compiled:**
```
brushed anodized aluminum with matte black polymer and frosted glass accents, soft key light from upper left with subtle rim light and controlled shadow falloff, gunmetal gray and deep navy palette with cool silver highlights, premium product photography with clean industrial aesthetic, ultra-detailed high realism, no color bleed no plastic-looking surfaces
```

